			<unit id="125" translate="yes">
				<originalData>
					<data id="id1">[</data>
					<data id="id2">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/windows/apps/dn926644)</data>
					<data id="id3">**</data>
					<data id="id4">**</data>
				</originalData>
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>The <pc dataRefEnd="id2" dataRefStart="id1" id="p1"><pc dataRefEnd="id4" dataRefStart="id3" id="p2">ExposurePriorityVideoControl</pc></pc>, when enabled, evaluates the video frames from the capture device to determine if the video is capturing a low-light scene.</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
			<unit id="126" translate="yes">
				<segment state="initial">
					<source>If so, the control lowers the frame rate of the captured video in order to increase the exposure time for each frame and improve the visual quality of the captured video.</source>
				</segment>
			</unit>
